1 packet Baby Leaves
300 g Diced Chicken
1 packet Cream
1 Broccoli
2 packet Potato
1 packet Dijon Mustard
1 drizzle olive oil
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
0.13 tsp salt
¼ tsp pepper

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water over high heat until easily pierced with a fork, 12-15 minutes. Drain and return to the pan.
• Add the butter and milk to potato and season generously with salt. Mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

• Meanwhile, cut broccoli (see ingredients) into small florets, then roughly chop stalk.
• Add broccoli and a splash of water to a microwave-safe bowl, then cover with a damp paper towel.
• Microwave broccoli on high until just tender, 2-4 minutes.
• Drain broccoli, then return to the bowl. Add baby leaves, season with salt and pepper, drizzle with olive oil and toss to combine. Cover to keep warm.

• While veggies are steaming, in a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook diced chicken, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium. Stir in cream (see ingredients), Dijon mustard, the salt and pepper, tossing chicken to coat, 1 minute.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it is no longer pink inside.

• Divide mash, steamed greens and creamy mustard chicken between plates. Spoon over any remaining sauce from pan to serve. Enjoy!
ELEVATE ME: If you’ve added extra ingredients to your recipe, sprinkle over Parmesan cheese and flaked almonds. Cut lemon into wedges, add a generous
squeeze of lemon juice and serve with any remaining wedges.